The paper discusses probabilistic graphical models, specifically Bayesian Networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the impact of uncertainty on the proposed quantum Bayesian Network, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also touches on the mathematical derivation of quantum interference terms, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of heuristics on human decision making, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
